\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.1}{\ignorespaces The unified benchmark: competitive ratio (mean, 95\% CI) versus prediction quality, for the three panels. Naive followers (MPD under adversarial, FollowPrediction) dip below the advice-free floor; the robust algorithms do not.}}{22}{figure.4.1}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.2}{\ignorespaces The consistency--robustness plane, one point per algorithm (consistency = ratio under perfect advice; robustness = worst ratio across advice quality; the data of Table 4.1). Dashed lines mark the advice-free floor, dotted the oracle ceiling. Naive followers (MPD, FollowPrediction) buy consistency with robustness; the structural augmentations give up little of either; TestAndMatch sits nearest the ideal top-right corner; the combiner stays pinned at the floor point.}}{23}{figure.4.2}\protected@file@percent }
